align-content.discription: Specifies the alignment between the lines inside a flexible container when the items do not use all available space

align-items.discription: Specifies the alignment for items inside a flexible container

align-self.discription: Specifies the alignment for selected items inside a flexible container

all.discription: The all property resets all properties, apart from unicode-bidi and direction, to their initial or inherited value.

animation.discription: The shorthand property for all animation properties

animation-delay.discription: Sets when an animation starts. The animation can start later, immediately from its beginning, or immediately and partway through the animation.

animation-direction.discription: Sets whether an animation should play forwards, backwards, or alternating back and forth.

animation-duration.discription: Sets the length of time that an animation takes to complete one cycle.

animation-fill-mode.discription: Sets how an animation applies styles to its target before and after its execution.

animation-iteration-count.discription: Specifies the number of times an animation should be played

animation-name.discription: Specifies a name for the @keyframes animation

animation-play-state.discription: Specifies whether the animation is running or paused

animation-timing-function.discription: Specifies the speed curve of an animation

backface-visibility.discription: Defines whether or not the back face of an element should be visible when facing the user

background.discription: A shorthand property for setting all the background properties in one declaration

background-attachment.discription: Sets whether a background image scrolls with the rest of the page, or is fixed

background-blend-mode.discription: Specifies the blending mode of each background layer (color/image)

background-clip.discription: Defines how far the background (color or image) should extend within an element

background-color.discription: Specifies the background color of an element

background-image.discription: Specifies one or more background images for an element

background-origin.discription: Specifies the origin position of a background image

background-position.discription: Specifies the position of a background image

background-repeat.discription: Sets if/how a background image will be repeated

background-size.discription: Specifies the size of the background images

border.discription: A shorthand property for border-width, border-style and border-color

border-bottom.discription: A shorthand property for setting all the bottom border properties in one declaration

border-bottom-color.discription: Sets the color of the bottom border

border-bottom-left-radius.discription: Defines the radius of the border of the bottom-left corner

border-bottom-right-radius.discription: Defines the radius of the border of the bottom-right corner

border-bottom-style.discription: Sets the style of the bottom border

border-bottom-width.discription: Sets the width of the bottom border

border-collapse.discription: Sets whether table borders should collapse into a single border or be separated

border-color.discription: Sets the color of the four borders

border-image.discription: A shorthand property for setting all the border-image-* properties

border-image-outset.discription: Specifies the amount by which the border image area extends beyond the border box

border-image-repeat.discription: Specifies whether the border image should be repeated, rounded or stretched

border-image-slice.discription: Specifies how to slice the border image

border-image-source.discription: Specifies the path to the image to be used as a border

border-image-width.discription: Specifies the width of the border image

border-left.discription: A shorthand property for setting all the left border properties in one declaration

border-left-color.discription: Sets the color of the left border

border-left-style.discription: Sets the style of the left border

border-left-width.discription: Sets the width of the left border

border-radius.discription:
A shorthand property for setting all the four border-*-radius properties. 
Setting 1 value will apply to all 4 corners, 
Setting 2 values will pair the opposite corners, 
Setting 3 will set the top-left, the top-right and bottom-left, and the bottom-right, 
Setting 4 values will apply the 4 radii clockwise starting from the top-left

border-right.discription: A shorthand property for setting all the right border properties in one declaration

border-right-color.discription: Sets the color of the right border

border-right-style.discription: Sets the style of the right border

border-right-width.discription: Sets the width of the right border

border-spacing.discription: Sets the distance between the borders of adjacent cells

border-style.discription: Sets the style of the four borders

border-top.discription: A shorthand property for setting all the top border properties in one declaration

border-top-color.discription: Sets the color of the top border

border-top-left-radius.discription: Defines the radius of the border of the top-left corner

border-top-right-radius.discription: Defines the radius of the border of the top-right corner

border-top-style.discription: Sets the style of the top border

border-top-width.discription: Sets the width of the top border

border-width.discription: Sets the width of the four borders

bottom.discription: Sets the elements position, from the bottom of its parent element

box-decoration-break.discription: Sets the behavior of the background and border of an element at page-break, or, for in-line elements, at line-break.

box-shadow.discription: Attaches one or more shadows to an element

box-sizing.discription: Defines how the width and height of an element are calculated: should they include padding and borders, or not

break-after.discription: Specifies the page-, column-, or region-break behavior after the generated box

break-before.discription: Specifies the page-, column-, or region-break behavior before the generated box

break-inside.discription: Specifies the page-, column-, or region-break behavior inside the generated box

caption-side.discription: Specifies the placement of a table caption

caret-color.discription: Specifies the color of the cursor (caret) in inputs, textareas, or any element that is editable

clear.discription: Specifies on which sides of an element floating elements are not allowed to float

column-count.discription: Specifies the number of columns an element should be divided into

column-fill.discription: Specifies how to fill columns, balanced or not

column-gap.discription: Specifies the gap between the columns

column-rule.discription: A shorthand property for setting all the column-rule-* properties

column-rule-color.discription: Specifies the color of the rule between columns

column-rule-style.discription: Specifies the style of the rule between columns

column-rule-width.discription: Specifies the width of the rule between columns

columns.discription: A shorthand property for setting column-width and column-count

column-span.discription: Specifies how many columns an element should span across

content.discription: Used with the :before and :after pseudo-elements, to insert generated content

counter-increment.discription: Increases or decreases the value of one or more CSS counters

counter-reset.discription: Creates or resets one or more CSS counters

cursor.discription: Specifies the mouse cursor to be displayed when pointing over an element

display.discription: Specifies how a certain HTML element should be displayed

empty-cells.discription: Specifies whether or not to display borders and background on empty cells in a table

filter.discription: Defines effects (e.g. blurring or color shifting) on an element before the element is displayed

flex.discription: Specifies the length of the item, relative to the rest

flex-basis.discription: Specifies the initial length of a flexible item

flex-direction.discription: Specifies the direction of the flexible items

flex-flow.discription: A shorthand property for the flex-direction and the flex-wrap properties

flex-grow.discription: Specifies how much the item will grow relative to the rest

flex-shrink.discription: Specifies how the item will shrink relative to the rest

flex-wrap.discription: Specifies whether the flexible items should wrap or not

float.discription: Specifies whether or not a box should float

font.discription: Sets all the font properties in one declaration

font-family.discription: Specifies the font family for text

font-feature-settings.discription: Allows control over advanced typographic features in OpenType fonts

font-kerning.discription: Controls the usage of the kerning information (how letters are spaced)

font-size.discription: Specifies the font size of text

font-size-adjust.discription: Preserves the readability of text when font fallback occurs

font-stretch.discription: Selects a normal, condensed, or expanded face from a font family

font-style.discription: Specifies the font style for text

font-variant.discription: Specifies whether or not a text should be displayed in a small-caps font

font-variant-caps.discription: Controls the usage of alternate glyphs for capital letters

font-variant-east-asian.discription: Controls the usage of alternate glyphs for East Asian scripts (e.g Japanese and Chinese)

font-variant-ligatures.discription: Controls which ligatures and contextual forms are used in textual content of the elements it applies to

font-variant-numeric.discription: Controls the usage of alternate glyphs for numbers, fractions, and ordinal markers

font-variant-position.discription: Controls the usage of alternate glyphs of smaller size positioned as superscript or subscript regarding the baseline of the font

font-weight.discription: Specifies the weight of a font

grid-area.discription: Either specifies a name for the grid item, or this property is a shorthand property for the grid-row-start, grid-column-start, grid-row-end, and grid-column-end properties

grid-auto-flow.discription: Specifies how auto-placed items are inserted in the grid

grid-column.discription: A shorthand property for the grid-column-start and the grid-column-end properties

grid-column-end.discription: Specifies where to end the grid item

grid-column-gap.discription: Specifies the size of the gap between columns

grid-column-start.discription: Specifies where to start the grid item

grid-gap.discription: A shorthand property for the grid-row-gap and grid-column-gap properties

grid-row.discription: A shorthand property for the grid-row-start and the grid-row-end properties

grid-row-end.discription: Specifies where to end the grid item

grid-row-gap.discription: Specifies the size of the gap between rows

grid-row-start.discription: Specifies where to start the grid item

grid-template.discription: A shorthand property for the grid-template-rows, grid-template-columns and grid-areas properties

grid-template-areas.discription: Specifies how to display columns and rows, using named grid items

grid-template-columns.discription: Specifies the size of the columns, and how many columns in a grid layout

grid-template-rows.discription: Specifies the size of the rows in a grid layout

hanging-punctuation.discription: Specifies whether a punctuation character may be placed outside the line box

height.discription: Sets the height of an element

hyphens.discription: Sets how to split words to improve the layout of paragraphs

image-orientation.discription: Specifies a rotation in the right or clockwise direction that a user agent applies to an image (This property is likely going to be deprecated and its functionality moved to HTML)

image-rendering.discription: Gives a hint to the browser about what aspects of an image are most important to preserve when the image is scaled

justify-content.discription: Specifies the alignment between the items inside a flexible container when the items do not use all available space

left.discription: Specifies the left position of a positioned element

letter-spacing.discription: Increases or decreases the space between characters in a text

list-style.discription: Sets all the properties for a list in one declaration

list-style-image.discription: Specifies an image as the list-item marker

list-style-position.discription: Specifies if the list-item markers should appear inside or outside the content flow

list-style-type.discription: Specifies the type of list-item marker

margin.discription: Sets all the margin properties in one declaration

margin-bottom.discription: Sets the bottom margin of an element

margin-left.discription: Sets the left margin of an element

margin-right.discription: Sets the right margin of an element

margin-top.discription: Sets the top margin of an element

max-height.discription: Sets the maximum height of an element

max-width.discription: Sets the maximum width of an element

min-height.discription: Sets the minimum height of an element

min-width.discription: Sets the minimum width of an element

object-fit.discription: Specifies how the contents of a replaced element should be fitted to the box established by its used height and width

object-position.discription: Specifies the alignment of the replaced element inside its box

opacity.discription: Sets the opacity level for an element

order.discription: Sets the order of the flexible item, relative to the rest

orphans.discription: Sets the minimum number of lines that must be left at the bottom of a page when a page break occurs inside an element

outline.discription: Sets all the outline properties in one declaration

outline-color.discription: Sets the color of an outline

outline-offset.discription: Offsets an outline, and draws it beyond the border edge

outline-style.discription: Sets the style of an outline

outline-width.discription: Sets the width of an outline

overflow.discription: Specifies what happens if content overflows an element's box

overflow-wrap.discription: Specifies whether or not the browser may break lines within words in order to prevent overflow (when a string is too long to fit its containing box)

overflow-x.discription: Specifies whether or not to clip the left/right edges of the content, if it overflows the element's content area

overflow-y.discription: Specifies whether or not to clip the top/bottom edges of the content, if it overflows the element's content area

padding.discription: Sets all the padding properties in one declaration

padding-bottom.discription: Sets the bottom padding of an element

padding-left.discription: Sets the left padding of an element

padding-right.discription: Sets the right padding of an element

padding-top.discription: Sets the top padding of an element

page-break-after.discription: Sets the page-breaking behavior after an element

page-break-before.discription: Sets the page-breaking behavior before an element

page-break-inside.discription: Sets the page-breaking behavior inside an element

perspective.discription: Specifies the perspective on how 3D elements are viewed

perspective-origin.discription: Specifies the position that the user is looking at the element

pointer-events.discription: The pointer-events property defines whether or not an element reacts to pointer events.

position.discription: Specifies the type of positioning method used for an element (static, relative, absolute or fixed)

quotes.discription: Sets the type of quotation marks for embedded quotations

resize.discription: Specifies whether or not an element is resizable by the user

right.discription: Specifies the right position of a positioned element

table-layout.discription: Sets the layout algorithm to be used for a table

tab-size.discription: Specifies the length of the tab-character

text-align.discription: Specifies the horizontal alignment of text

text-align-last.discription: Describes how the last line of a block or a line right before a forced line break is aligned when text-align is "justify"

text-combine-upright.discription: Specifies the combination of multiple characters into the space of a single character

text-decoration.discription: Specifies the decoration added to text

text-decoration-color.discription: Specifies the color of the text-decoration

text-decoration-line.discription: Specifies the type of line in a text-decoration

text-decoration-style.discription: Specifies the style of the line in a text decoration

text-indent.discription: Specifies the indentation of the first line in a text-block

text-justify.discription: Specifies the justification method used when text-align is "justify"

text-orientation.discription: Defines the orientation of the text in a line

text-overflow.discription: Specifies what should happen when text overflows the containing element

text-underline-position.discription: Specifies the position of the underline which is set using the text-decoration property

top.discription: Specifies the top position of a positioned element

touch-action.discription: Sets how an element's region can be manipulated by a touchscreen user (for example, by zooming features built into the browser)

transform.discription: Applies a 2D or 3D transformation to an element

transform-origin.discription: Allows you to change the position on transformed elements

transform-style.discription: Specifies how nested elements are rendered in 3D space

transition.discription: A shorthand property for setting the four transition properties

transition-delay.discription: Specifies when the transition effect will start

transition-duration.discription: Specifies how many seconds or milliseconds a transition effect takes to complete

transition-property.discription: Specifies the name of the CSS property the transition effect is for

transition-timing-function.discription: Specifies the speed curve of the transition effect

unicode-bidi.discription: Used together with the direction property to set or return whether the text should be overridden to support multiple languages in the same document

user-select.discription: Specifies whether the text of an element can be selected

vertical-align.discription: Sets the vertical alignment of an element

visibility.discription: Specifies whether or not an element is visible

white-space.discription: Specifies how white-space inside an element is handled

widows.discription: Sets the minimum number of lines that must be left at the top of a page when a page break occurs inside an element

width.discription: Sets the width of an element

word-break.discription: Specifies line breaking rules for non-CJK scripts

word-spacing.discription: Increases or decreases the space between words in a text

word-wrap.discription: Allows long, unbreakable words to be broken and wrap to the next line

z-index.discription: Sets the stack order of a positioned element
